Censorship is trending up on the clearnet. I've run some blogs and sharing sites in the past that could've landed me in trouble today, mostly because of vigilantism (people calling my workplace), but police is arresting people for things they say on social media, that I'd consider tame where I live now (eg. jokes about kebab delivery being late when a truck ran through a crowd). I'd rather switch to decentralized pseudonymous internet while it's still in development and unproven now, and not in a few years time when censorship gets worse. I trust networks like tor and i2p do their job well, but I'd like to be able to turn my pc off!
